  <p>
I think this approach to leadership was successful within the design team, where I scaled the team from less than 10 people to more than 60 people over a 3-year period. 

In that time we collaboratively created a progression framework, wrote design standards, introduced junior roles, created training plans, and sourced external training partners, making sure we continually invested in and developed our in-house team.  
 
</p>
<p>

However when leading the design profession and representing design across the organisation vulnerability could be seen as a weakness, especially in an organisation that has competing priorities and subcultures.
</p>


