<p>
This new approach is more aligned to a transactional leadership style.
Transactional leadership is explained by Kuhnert and Lewis as giving followers something they want in exchange for something the leader wants. 
</p>
<p>Borgmann, Rowold and Bormann also describe transactional leadership as setting out clear expectations and the required standards of performance, in order to gain the commitment and motivation of followers	
</p>


