<p>
Although the new approach was successful in the sense that the project was set up the way I wanted it to be.

The more direct approach meant there was less alignment and therefore less trust between myself and the team.

As Lencioni says an absence of trust is the most severe dysfunction that a team can have. Without trust, productive work and growth are almost impossible. 

</p>

    <figure>
    <div class="third">
